title: Yreka High varsity volleyball team downs Central Valley in four games
text: Yreka High varsity volleyball team downs Central Valley in four games Comment By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com   Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 12:00 PM Updated at 3:20 PM By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 12:00 PM Updated at 3:20 PM YREKA The Yreka High varsity volleyball team downed Central Valley at home 22-25, 25-20, 25-20, 25-23 in Northern Athletic League action on Tuesday. Taylor Callahan had 15 kills and six blocks for Yreka. Gabby Lovelace had 50 digs, while Rebekah Kimball had 12 service points. Yreka improved to 15-14 overall and 2-3 in the NAL. CentralValley fell to 2-17 overall and 0-5 in the NAL. In the junior varsity contest, Yreka downed Central Valley 25-19, 23-25, 15-11. In the freshman contest, Yreka improved to 4-1 in the Northern Athletic League by downing Central Valley 25-21, 25-15. All three Yreka volleyball teams play at Anderson on Thursday. By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com   Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 12:00 PM Updated at 3:20 PM
